President Donald Trump arrives for the daily briefing on the novel coronavirus.
There are many ironies of the COVID-19 era, perhaps too many to count.
For decades, we’ve persuaded ourselves that there is some probable correlation between being able to capture attention on camera and complex public leadership abilities.
Hours of screens within screens that might really be Zooms now force us into canned reality show tropes: “Look at me!
The centering of faces in screens, the focusing of faces on screens.